Description: Mode-S demodulator for ADS-B reception via SDR
 stream1090 is a CRC-based Mode-S demodulator that reads IQ samples
 from an Airspy or RTL-SDR dongle and outputs raw Mode-S message frames
 to stdout. It is designed to feed a decoder such as readsb or dump1090-fa
 via socat over TCP.
 .
 Unlike preamble-based approaches, stream1090 maintains a set of shift
 registers and identifies messages purely by CRC sum, which avoids missing
 messages due to a missed preamble and enables error correction.
